---
title: Homepage
metas:
  title: HHYurdagul - Homepage
  description: Homepage of hhyurdagul.com
---

<header class="hero container page-enter">
  <p class="mono-prompt cursor-blink">
    <span class="prompt-user">hhyurdagul</span><span class="prompt-host">:</span><span class="prompt-dir">~</span><span
      class="prompt-sym">λ</span> <span class="prompt-cmd">whoami</span>
  </p>
  <h1>Hasan Hüseyin<br><span>Yurdagül</span></h1>
  <p class="hero-desc">Machine learning engineer. Consultant. Deep thinker.<br>I build things from first principles.
  </p>

  <div class="tags-container">
    <span class="tag">ML Engineer</span>
    <span class="tag">Consultant</span>
    <span class="tag">Arch + Hyprland</span>
    <span class="tag">Neovim → Helix</span>
    <span class="tag">27</span>
    <span class="tag">Turkey</span>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="container">
  <div class="section-line"></div>

  <section id="about" class="section-padding fade-in">
    <h2 class="section-title">/about</h2>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>I'm a <span class="text-white">machine learning engineer</span> working remotely from Turkey, and a
          consultant to R&D Centers on AI and ML. I hold a degree in Computer Engineering and I'm currently pursuing
          my Master's in Artificial Intelligence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-image-wrapper">
        <img alt="Cow — the real animal" class="about-image" src="/assets/cow.jpeg">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-line"></div>

  <section id="prose" class="section-padding fade-in">
    <h2 class="section-title">/Articles</h2>
    <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Thinking on engineering, math, systems, and life.</p>

    <div class="prose-list">
      {{ for article of search.pages("type=article showcase=true", "date=desc") }}
      {{ set readingTime = article.content |> extractReadingTime }}
      {{ comp.ProseItem({
      url: article.url,
      title: article.title,
      date: article.date,
      readingTime: readingTime
      }) }}
      {{ /for }}
    </div>

    <a class="btn all-entries-btn" href="/articles/">
      All entries <span>→</span>
    </a>
  </section>

  <div class="section-line"></div>

  <section id="projects" class="section-padding fade-in">
    <h2 class="section-title">/projects</h2>
    <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">Case studies of systems I've built end-to-end.</p>

    <div class="home-project-list">
      {{ for project of search.pages("type=project", "date=desc") }}
      {{ set readingTime = project.content |> extractReadingTime }}
      {{ comp.ProjectCard({
      url: project.url,
      title: project.title,
      desc: project.desc,
      date: project.date,
      readingTime: readingTime,
      status: project.status,
      tags: project.tags
      }) }}
      {{ /for }}
    </div>

    <a class="btn all-entries-btn" href="/projects/">
      All projects <span>→</span>
    </a>

    <style component>
    .home-project-list {
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    </style>
  </section>

  <div class="section-line"></div>

  <section id="tech" class="section-padding fade-in">
    <h2 class="section-title">/tech</h2>
    <p class="text-muted" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">I've been a Linux user since 2016. The journey has been long —
      from Mint to Arch, a detour through NixOS (beautiful pain), a macOS era (M1 was magic), and finally back home to
      Arch + Hyprland. Freedom matters. Window managers matter.</p>

    {{ comp.TerminalBox({
    title: "distro_hop.sh",
    rows: [
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2016] Linux Mint # the beginning" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2016] Ubuntu # the obvious next" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2016] Pop!_OS # the hyped children" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2016] Fedora # usable, but not fresh" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2016] Manjaro # intro to arch, but gentle" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2017] Arch Linux # the real deal" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2020] NixOS # beautiful pain" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2021] macOS (M1) # incredible hardware" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2022] Arch (again) # yearning freedom" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2022] macOS (M1) # disgusting software, but unbeatable hardware" },
    { prompt: "$", text: "[2025] Arch + Hyprland # returning home" }
    ]
    }) }}

    <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
      <h3 class="section-subtitle" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">Languages I enjoy</h3>
      <div class="lang-tags">
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #93c5fd;">Python</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #a3a3a3;">C</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #fb923c;">Rust</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #facc15;">Zig</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #4ade80;">Odin</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #fdba74;">OCaml</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #93c5fd;">Lua</span>
        <span class="lang-tag" style="color: #fde047;">JS/TS</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-dark" style="font-size: 0.75rem;">I try every paradigm. Systems programming, functional,
        scripting — understanding the spectrum makes you a better engineer. I create things from scratch to understand
        them from first principles, it takes time, but it's worth it.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tech-grids">
      {{ comp TerminalBox {title: "cs_amazement.log", marginZero: true} }}
      <p>The first thing that amazed me in CS was the <span class='text-white'>linked list</span> — this
        elegant, recursive data structure where every node points to the next. Then <span class='text-white'>automata
          theory</span>: the idea that a simple machine with states and transitions could model computation itself.</p>
      {{ /comp }}



      {{ comp TerminalBox {title: "ai_amazement.log", marginZero: true} }}
      <p>In AI, <span class="text-white">autoencoders</span> blew my mind — the idea that a network could learn
        to compress and reconstruct, discovering the essence of data. And <span class="text-white">GANs</span>: two
        networks battling each other, creating something from nothing. Adversarial creation is pure genius.</p>
      {{ /comp }}
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem;">
      {{ comp.TerminalBox({
      title: "editor_journey.md",
      rows: [
      { prompt: "~", text: "neovim ── longtime user, broke every update" },
      { prompt: "~", text: "helix ── current editor, good defaults, stable and fine" },
      { prompt: "~", text: "" },
      { prompt: "~", text: "# I value my time more as I age" },
      { prompt: "~", text: "# I don't have enough time to configure everything." },
      { prompt: "~", text: "# I need things delivered, but I must be able to change them." },
      { prompt: "~", text: "# Helix gave me the balance of freedom, and sanity" }
      ]
      }) }}
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="section-line"></div>

  <section id="work" class="section-padding fade-in">
    <h2 class="section-title">/work</h2>
    <div class="work-list">
      {{ comp.WorkItem({
        company: "Universal Software",
        title: "Head of R&D AI",
        dates: "Jan 2024 - Present",
        loc: "Istanbul, Turkey (Hybrid)",
        url: "https://www.universalyazilim.com/",
        description: "Lead the AI R&D division directing municipal and enterprise AI strategy. Deployed LLM and sentence-similarity pipelines for support ticketing optimization that cut response times in half, and built automated categorization systems using sentiment embeddings. Also serving as the technical lead for international Horizon Europe consortium proposals such as FloodGuard and Pre-act.",
        tech: ["Python", "LLMs", "Transformers", "Word Embeddings", "TF-IDF", "Clustering", "Horizon Europe Scoping"]
      }) }}

      {{ comp.WorkItem({
        company: "R&D AI/ML Consultancy",
        title: "Independent Consultant",
        dates: "Sep 2020 - Present",
        loc: "Turkey (Remote)",
        description: "Provide strategic machine learning, time-series forecasting, and R&D consultancy for flagship e-commerce and fintech platforms. Built semantic search and image classification systems for Inveon, developed end-to-end pricing and churn prediction pipelines on Azure for Moka, and shipped forecasting tools for Ikas and Robokobi.",
        tech: ["Python", "FastAPI", "Streamlit", "Docker", "Kubernetes", "Azure", "Time-Series Forecasting", "Recommender Systems"]
      }) }}

      {{ comp.WorkItem({
        company: "M.Sc. Artificial Intelligence",
        title: "Thesis Research",
        dates: "Aug 2023 - Feb 2026",
        loc: "Çukurova University",
        description: "Completed Master's in Artificial Intelligence with a thesis focused on monocular depth estimation and attention-driven vision networks. Developed models capable of estimating an object's physical length from a single photograph without requiring physical reference markers in the frame.",
        tech: ["Computer Vision", "Depth Estimation", "Attention Models", "PyTorch", "Deep Learning"]
      }) }}
    </div>

    <a class="btn all-entries-btn" href="/work/">
      Full work history <span>→</span>
    </a>
  </section>

</div>